‚ô° the more carbs you burn during exercise---the more fat you burn post-workout and vice-versa‚Å£
‚ô° eating before exercise increases EPOC (excess post-exercise oxygen consumption) which is the number of calories burned during a post-workout period. Since most of our calories we burn come from fat--post workout this means more fat is burned as opposed to during exercise‚Å£

Why is it so important to feed your kids healthy food?‚Å£
‚Å£
I know it's tempting to just pop instant mac n cheese in the microwave and call it good...I get it mama! Some days that's all I can muster, too!‚Å£
‚Å£
But, that shouldn't be what your kids rely on for nutrition every day.‚Å£
‚Å£
Kids need healthy fats and carbs just like you! ‚Å£
‚Å£
Artificial colors and dyes can make our little humans moody or hyperactive. It's our jobs as parents to set them up for success while they're young. ‚Å£
‚Å£
My kids know we eat a fruit or veggie with every meal. I also try to include plenty of healthy fats like full fat yogurt, cheese, or whole milk. ‚Å£
‚Å£
When kids eat too many refined carbs it makes it hard for them to focus. Include healthy proteins whenever possible. ‚Å£
‚Å£
If my kids want a bagel for breakfast, I'll always add an egg and sausage. And, instead of instant pancakes that are loaded in carbs we'll meal-prep their breakfast on Sundays with Kodiak pancake or waffle mix. Little things like this make a big difference in their development and what they will crave when they get older. ‚Å£
‚Å£
My mom used to make cream of wheat when I was young and I remember being pumped when I got to college I could buy my own sugary cereal instead!!! Then, when I got home, I realized how crappy I felt when I ate it I went back to my oats! üòÇ‚Å£
‚Å£
Our kids will only eat what we feed them. ‚Å£
‚Å£
Remember, YOU are the one buying the groceries. Studies suggest it could take up to 5 times before our kids acquire the taste for certain foods. So, if you serve something they don't like...don't get discouraged. Just try again another day. Do them a favor and make it healthy!‚Å£
‚Å£
What's your favorite go-to meal for kids? I need more!‚Å£
